The lecture focuses on microeconomics, a branch of economics that focuses on the behavior and decision-making of individual consumers, businesses, and industries. Microeconomics explores the concept of supply and demand, which refers to the interaction between supply and supply, and the opportunity cost of making a choice. It also looks at how businesses and consumers respond to price changes, a concept known as elasticity. The concept of opportunity cost, which is the idea that when we make a choice, we are giving up something else, is also discussed. The lecture concludes by emphasizing the importance of understanding the role of microeconomic forces in shaping the economy.